Have a program that:

- Connects to multiple IRC servers
- various modules, interface:
  init()
  loop()
  handle_data()
  finish()
- modules: 
 - replicate_simple (only does replication when client is connected)
 - replicate_advanced (tries to figure out what and who is in the channels and stores channel logs)
 - log (logs data to files)

Configuration file syntax:

name = value

{
  host = irc.freenode.net
  pass = 
  port = 6667
  nick = 
  }
	  file = "log.so";
  }
}

ctrlproxy.h: 'global' include file - only include file used by modules
dlinklist.h: Tridge's double linked list defines
internals.h: Stuff not used by modules
server.c: communication with server, parsing of lines
- SERVER *connect_to_server(char *name, int port, char *nick);
- loop(SERVER *server); /* Checks server socket for input and calls loop() on all of it's modules */
modules.c: 
- MODULE_CONTEXT *load_module(SERVER *s, char *name);
- unload_module(MODULE_CONTEXT *); /* Removes specified module from server and unloads module if necessary */
conf.c:
- load_conf_file(char *file);
- get_conf_context(struct module_context *c, char *name);
- get_conf_server(struct server *s, char *name);
- get_conf_global(char *name);
